-- Bangpakong, Dusit Thani, Pranda, SPCG: Thailand Equity Preview
-- B y   T o n y   J o r d a n
-- 2012-03-29T02:43:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/bangpakong-dusit-thani-pranda-spcg-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Thailand  trading.  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close yesterday.  The  SET Index (SET)  fell 0.3 percent to 1,204.01.  Bangpakong Terminal Pcl (BTC)  : The cargo company plans
to sell 15.9 percent of its Platinum Container Lines Co. unit,
it said in a regulatory filing. The shares were unchanged at
0.36 baht.  Dusit Thani Pcl (DTC)  : The hotel operator will stop
hiring new workers because a planned increase in Thailand’s
minimum wage will increase costs, Post Today reported, citing
Chief Executive Officer Chanin Donavanik. The shares rose 0.7
percent to 34.75 baht.  Pranda Jewelry Pcl (PRANDA)  : The jewelry producer’s
first-quarter revenue will exceed last year’s because of strong
demand in Asian markets, Krungthep Turakij reported, citing
Chief Financial Officer Sunanta Tiasuwan. The shares were
unchanged at 6.4 baht.  SPCG Pcl (SPCG)  (SPCG TB): The alternative energy company may set
up a 10 billion-baht ($324 million) infrastructure fund to
finance 18 new solar power projects, Kao Hoon reported, citing
an unidentified company official. The shares fell 1.3 percent to
15.5 baht.  To contact the reporter on this story:
